node.text:
Why have pets when you can train wild macaws 🦜 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on explorerfervor.com (link in my bio: @explorerfervor) 

come every morning for food. In Spanish macaws are called guacamayas, these are native to Caracas Venezuela.

📽 TT bbitoslove
📍 Caracas, Venezuela

node.text:
The beauty of the Faroe Islands 🤍Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on explorerfervor.com (link in my bio: @explorerfervor) 

The Faroe Islands are made up of 18 islands located about 200 miles north-northwest of Scotland and about halfway between Norway & Iceland.  The islands are rugged and rocky with some low peaks; the coasts are mostly cliffs. 

Do you think you'd be interested in visiting? 🇫🇴 

Photos & videos by:
1. @dope4travel 
2. @golden_heart 
3. @patheight 
4. @luigichiurchi

node.text:
Diving deep and free, just the water and me 😌Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @explorerfervor 

Ginnie Springs is a privately owned park in Gilchrist County about 6.5 miles (10.5 km) northwest of High Springs, Florida, USA. It is located on the south side of the Santa Fe River, to which it is connected. The water is clear and cold and there are accessible caverns with a sand and limestone bottom.

Ginnie Springs has been privately owned by the Wray family since 1971 and began functioning in 1976. In the mid-1990s when scuba diving grew in popularity, Bob Wray opened the springs to the public. The popularity of Ginnie took off and it became a nationally renowned diving spot which is still largely popular today.

📽 @andrewdesloover w/ @bjgriffinmusic
📍Ginnie Springs, Florida

node.text:
We're loving @anamaria's sight of the Adriatic Sea in Hvar Island, Croatia's Adriatic Sea nook that's sought-after by even the most exquisite travelers. 🏝Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @explorerfervor 

Hvar, a Croatian island in the Adriatic Sea, is best known as a summer resort. Highlights of the port town Hvar include its 13th-century walls, a hilltop fortress and a main square anchored by the Renaissance-era Hvar Cathedral. The island also features beaches such as Dubovica and inland lavender fields. Boat excursions serve the nearby Pakleni Islands, which have secluded beaches and coves.✨

Have you heard of this island and have you ever been to Croatia? 🇭🇷

📽 @anamaria
📍 Hvar Island, Croatia
🎶 will.i.am - Good Morning

Devil’s Pool is a natural pool of water that’s situated atop of Victoria Falls, renown for being among the largest waterfalls in the world. Right on the edge of this massive waterfall, a calm pool of water forms.

This is known as the Devil’s Pool Victoria Falls. And daring visitors can actually swim in this pool straddling the edge of Victoria Falls!

📽 @abenafrica
📍Zambia and Zimbabwe
🎶 Ikson - Apart

node.text:
Umbrella tree 🌳 Get your photos posted in our account, apply for a feature visiting explorerfervor.com 👉🏼 the link is in our bio: @explorerfervor 

How impressive is this holm oak? Known as the umbrella tree. Once a year two gardeners climb up into its crown on ladders, and for two weeks they prune the tree like a skirt as they meticulously trim it into shape. Its healing powers helped James Bond recuperate – Casino Royale.

📽 @brigrc
📍Villa del Balbianello, Como, Italy

This purring cheeta is the sweetest thing in the wild @nature 🐆We can post your pictures in our account. Check the link in our bio for more info: @explorerfervor 

Tag someone you’d like to cuddle like this 👇

📹 @wildcatcentre
